blend with attitudes in God. </div><div class="t m145 xb7 h4 y7c4 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">We should ask in order to share our bless-</div><div class="t m16fc xb7 h4 y171d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ing with those in need. There is no one </div><div class="t m459 xb7 h4 y205f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">time to pray—we may pray in all circum-</div><div class="t m1bb xb7 h4 ya24 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">stances and places and times. Persistence </div><div class="t maf1 xb7 h4 y1133 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and heart&apos;s need will always gain an an-</div><div class="t m344 xb7 h4 y1499 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">swer from our prayer-hearing God. </div><div class="t m42f x91 h13 y477 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON OUTLINE </div><div class="t m7a0 xab h13 y72c ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m187 x54 h13 y72c ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Teach Us to Pray </div><div class="t m22c xb3 h13 y3ad ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 11:1-4 </div><div class="t mec2 x4b h13 y575 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m9ba x54 h13 y575 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A Friend Comes Asking </div><div class="t mf40 xb3 h13 y2ee ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 11:5-8 </div><div class="t m2ca xab h13 yf82 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m20fe x54 h13 y675 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Widow in Need </div><div class="t mf40 xb3 h13 y428 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 18:1-8 </div><div class="t mb90 x4b h13 y530 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m23a xb3 h13 y530 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Snob </div><div class="t m165a xb3 h13 y7a1 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 18:9-12 </div><div class="t mb90 xab h13 yf85 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m73e xb3 h13 yf85 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Heart&apos;s Cry </div><div class="t mfde xb3 h13 y96c ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 18:13, 14 </div><div class="t m9b x4b h13 y872 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m1224 xb3 h13 y55 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Peter—Pharisee or Publican? </div><div cl